Paper: hep-th/9703185

Date: 1997-03-26

Title: N=2 Supersymmetric Gauged O(3) Sigma Model

Authors: Kyoungtae Kimm and Bukyung Sul

Comments: 7 pages, Latex, no figures

Journal-ref: J.Korean Phys.Soc. 32 (1998) 609-611

We discuss the N=2 supersymmetric extension of the gauged O(3) sigma model in(2+1) dimensions with an abelian Chern-Simons term. It is shown that theself-dual potential and the Bogomolny relations naturally appear asconsequences of extended supersymmetry.